This paper discusses the challenges of making web annotations persistent over time, which is a core issue in digital libraries and web architecture. The paper specifically focuses on the temporal features of the Open Annotation data model and the Memento framework, which are relevant to the areas of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), web architecture (cs.WEB), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
